The paper proposes an efficient strategy for training neural network based language models, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of modern architectures and matrix-matrix vector operations, which are common in deep learning and ML, suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of GPUs, which are commonly used in computer vision (CV) and neural networks (NE), indicating that cs.CV and cs.NE are also possible sub-categories.
